Nicholas Ninow has pleaded guilty to two counts of rape and possession of drugs. JOHANNESBURG - Judgment in the Dros rape trial is expected to be handed down on Monday. Last week, the eight-year-old girl raped in the toilets of a Dros restaurant by Nicholas Ninow testified via CCTV. Her mother also testified. Dros rape case: NPA says little girl did well Ninow has pleaded guilty to two counts of rape and possession of drugs. The state has said that it will argue for life imprisonment.